Sec. 13.121. DISPOSING OF CONDEMNED WEIGHING OR MEASURING
DEVICE. A person commits an offense if the person or the person's
servant or agent disposes of a weighing or measuring device condemned
under Section 13.111 or 13.120 in a manner contrary to those
sections.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1036, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.
Amended by:
Acts 2009, 81st Leg., R.S., Ch. 913 (H.B. 2925), Sec. 17, eff.
September 1, 2009.

